## Fix: Settings/Lakebase Connection tab — dropdowns not pre-selected on page load

### Context
In the Settings → Lakebase → Connection tab, the Project, Branch, and Database dropdowns were always shown blank on initial page load (only the Postgres schema field was pre-populated). The root cause: the stored `graph_engine_config` in the registry only has `schema` set by default; the `lakebase_project`, `lakebase_branch`, and `database` fields are empty until the user explicitly saves them via the cascading Load → Select flow. The `prefillLakebaseConnectionFromConfig()` JS function uses `_ensureSelectedOption(sel, value)` which returns immediately when `value` is empty — so those three dropdowns stayed blank.

### Fix
`SettingsService.get_graph_engine_config_result` now overlays env-var fallbacks (`LAKEBASE_PROJECT`, `LAKEBASE_BRANCH`, `PGDATABASE`/`LAKEBASE_DATABASE`) for any empty field before returning the config. This ensures the Connection tab always reflects the current platform binding even when the stored config is sparse.

### Changes

1. `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py` — `get_graph_engine_config_result` now merges env-var defaults for `lakebase_project`, `lakebase_branch`, and `database` before returning the config dict.

### Modified Files
- `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`

### Test Results
- Unit tests unaffected (env-var overlay only; no stored data changed).

---

## Fix: Settings/Lakebase Bulk loading tab — UC catalog not pre-selected; engine change missing catalog reload

### Context
Two related issues in the Bulk loading tab:
1. `prefillLakebaseConnectionFromConfig()` covered only the 4 Connection-tab cascading selects but not the `lakebaseUcCatalog` dropdown in the Bulk loading tab (managed_synced mode). When a `sync_uc_catalog` value was saved to the registry config, it would not be pre-selected after page load.
2. The `graphEngineSelect` change handler triggered the `loadLakebaseProjects` cascade but did not re-trigger `loadUcCatalogsForGraphEngine` even when the saved mode was `managed_synced`.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js` — `prefillLakebaseConnectionFromConfig` extended to call `_ensureSelectedOption` for `lakebaseUcCatalog`.
2. `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js` — `graphEngineSelect` change handler now triggers `loadUcCatalogsForGraphEngine()` when the saved sync mode is `managed_synced`.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`

### Test Results
- JS-only changes; no backend impact.

---

## Fix: App startup crash — `Any` not imported in UnityCatalog

### Context
After the Registry access-check feature was merged (`check_schema_access` / `check_volume_access`), the new method `check_schema_access` used `Dict[str, Any]` as its return type annotation but `Any` was never added to the `typing` import line. This raised `NameError: name 'Any' is not defined` at module load time, preventing the entire application from starting.

### Changes

1. `src/back/core/databricks/UnityCatalog.py` — added `Any` to the `from typing import …` statement (line 10).

### Modified Files
- `src/back/core/databricks/UnityCatalog.py`

### Test Results
- App starts cleanly. Full test suite unaffected (typing fix only).

---

## Fix: Runs page JS crash — `#runDetailsBody` null when modal missing from dtwin template

### Context
The Runs section is shared between the Domain page (`domain.html`) and the Knowledge Graph page (`dtwin.html`). The partial `_domain_runs.html` was included in `dtwin.html` but the `runDetailsModal` (with `id="runDetailsBody"`) was not yet added to that template. When a user clicked the details eye-button on the Runs section of the dtwin page, `showRunDetailsObj()` in `domain-runs.js` called `document.getElementById('runDetailsBody')`, got `null`, and crashed with `Uncaught TypeError: Cannot set properties of null (setting 'innerHTML')`.

### Fix
1. Added the `runDetailsModal` HTML to `dtwin.html` (at page level, outside `.sidebar-section`).
2. Added the `domain-runs.js` deferred script tag to `dtwin.html`.
3. Added a defensive null guard in `showRunDetailsObj()` with a `console.error` so any future modal-missing scenario fails gracefully instead of throwing.

### Changes

1. `src/front/templates/dtwin.html` — added run-details modal and `domain-runs.js` script.
2. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js` — null guard for `body` in `showRunDetailsObj()`.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/templates/dtwin.html`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js`

### Test Results
- Server restarted; updated template now served. Browser hard-refresh clears the stale page.

