## Feature: Domain menu restructure — Metadata section, Cockpit in Management, no separator

### Context
The Domain sidebar menu needed three UX improvements: the "Domain details" group label was a redundant separator before the nav links; Data Sources and Documents had no logical grouping; and Cockpit (domain health dashboard) belonged under Management rather than the general detail list.

### Changes

1. `src/front/config/menu_config.json` — domain menu:
   - `domain-main` group title set to `""` (hides the "Domain details" label).
   - New `domain-metadata` group ("Metadata") added after `domain-main`, containing Data Sources and Documents.
   - `validation` (Cockpit) moved from `domain-main` to `domain-management` at position 1 (before Audit trail).
2. `src/front/templates/partials/layout/_sidebar_nav.html` — sidebar-title div now only rendered when `group.title` is non-empty, preventing an empty spacer div.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/config/menu_config.json`
- `src/front/templates/partials/layout/_sidebar_nav.html`

### Test Results
- Visual: sidebar nav renders without the "Domain details" header; Metadata section visible; Cockpit is first item in Management.

