## Feature: Runs section auto-loads on navigation

### Context
Clicking the "Runs" sidebar link did nothing until the user manually hit the Refresh button. The section should load its data automatically on first visit.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js` — added two listeners:
   - `sidebarSectionChanged`: calls `loadDomainRuns()` when the `runs` section becomes active and data hasn't been loaded yet.
   - `DOMContentLoaded`: calls `loadDomainRuns()` if the page is opened with `runs` already the active section (e.g. deep-link `?section=runs`).

### Modified Files
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js`

### Test Results
- Navigating to Runs loads the table without requiring a manual Refresh click.

