## Fix: Knowledge Graph Explorer — right-click context menu hover invisible (white on white)

### Context
In the Knowledge Graph → Explorer (sigmagraph), right-clicking a node showed a context menu but hovering over items was invisible because `.graph-context-menu .ctx-item:hover` set `background: #ffffff` (white on white). The Ontology → Designer uses `.map-context-item:hover { background: #e8f4fd; color: #1a73e8; }` which is clearly visible.

### Fix
Updated `.graph-context-menu .ctx-item:hover` in `query-visualization.css` to use the same blue-tint hover style as the ontology map context menu.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/query/css/query-visualization.css` — `.ctx-item:hover` now uses `background: #e8f4fd; color: #1a73e8` and icon inherits the blue color on hover.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/static/query/css/query-visualization.css`

### Test Results
- Visual fix only; no logic changes.

