## Fix (correction): Knowledge Graph Explorer — context menu hover fix was in wrong CSS file

### Context
The previous fix targeted `.graph-context-menu .ctx-item:hover` in `query-visualization.css`, but `#sgContextMenu` and `#sgNodeContextMenu` have their own ID-scoped rules in `query-sigmagraph.css` that are more specific and override the class selector. Both ID rules had `background: #ffffff` on hover (white on white).

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/query/css/query-sigmagraph.css` — fixed `#sgContextMenu .ctx-item:hover` and `#sgNodeContextMenu .ctx-item:hover` to use `background: #e8f4fd; color: #1a73e8` with matching icon color.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/static/query/css/query-sigmagraph.css`
